begin_memory_text: At the beginning we talked about how covid impacted us and what it was like to deal with covid in our respective states.
middle_memory_text: Middle of our conversation was mostly about hobbies, things we liked doing for fun.  I gave her some recommendations for series to watch on Netflix and a game to try out on mobile.
end_memory_text: End of our conversation was mostly about how we hope covid will end and hopes for the new year.  We also talked about things we miss from before covid.
rest_of_day_open:
The rest of my week I think will be fairly uneventful, at least at work.  At work I'll be dealing with a lot of the same problems I deal with on a regular basis and during down time I'll be processing some images for printing on my personal laptop.

At home I think I will be preparing shelves to be painted to mount to the wall.  I'll also be donating blood on Tuesday so that'll be good.
critical_positive: We were both friendly with each other right off the bat.  We asked questions to get to know each other a little better and without judgement.  I talked about my hobbies and she was accepting of them and generally interested in what I had to say.  I listened to her hobbies and things she liked and gave information that may be helpful for that.
critical_negative: I feel like there wasn't anything that didn't work as well.  We both talked freely about topics that came to mind and there was only a small lull in the conversation before it picked back up again.  However I don't think that lull was due to a problem that either of us had.

begin_memory_text: At the beginning, we asked each other where we were (she's in Atlanta) and I'm TX, and I asked how things are there with Covid-19.  She said most places will have you wear a mask while here in TX, there is a mask mandate for all stores and retail (basically everywhere except outside)
middle_memory_text: We spoke about tv shows and Netflix, and she and her husband provided recommendations, including Magic for Humans and Hulu show ideas if I were to subscribe to Hulu
end_memory_text: We talked about Cirque du Soliel, and she had not seen that show.  She was also interested in seeing Shyn Chen (not sure if that is spelled correctly) and we spoke about enjoying going to conventions, talking to people and getting free swag at the vendor booths.  She showed one of cats on the video.
rest_of_day_open: I think my week will go well.  I am tired but glad it is Sunday and that I have tomorrow off from work.  I do not feel well physically but I am proud of myself for following through with this survey call because I wanted to do the right thing but was tempted to just go to bed.  But I would not want to leave someone hanging by not showing up.  This reminds me to do the right thing and the conversation was fine, so I think my week will go well.. Good karma.
critical_positive: I think we each tried to find some commonalities but we are very different.  She is a hard core gamer who has three cats, and I do not like cats, nor do I play traditional video games.  But we found out we each like comedies and were able to respect each other and talk about how things are where we live
critical_negative: I felt like she and I were very different.  She lives in a place where there is not restaurant food delivery since it is out of the delivery radius, she plays video games and seemed to be a bit bored at times.  I tried to keep the conversation going but sometimes it was hard.
